    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "Flat Folder Tree enables you to selectively breakout sub-folders under intermediate folders in the folder pane view. It does not alter your Thunderbird folder hierarchy or message storage. Instead, this add-on implements another folder pane view side-by-side with the existing ones like All, Unread, Unified, Recent and Favorites. That is, a new view named \"Flattened\" is added to the list of choices you have for folder views.\n\nAfter installing this add-on, three new commands will be added to the context menu of each folder in the folder tree view.\n\n<b>Breakout Subfolders</b>\nThis option brings out the subfolders of the selected folder and hides the parent folder itself. This is perfect for breaking out the special [Gmail] namespace imposed by Google Mail.\n\n<b>Promote Subfolders</b>\nThis option brings out the subfolders of the selected folder and still keeps the parent folder visible. This is perfect for IMAP servers where special folders are stored under INBOX.\n\n<b>Restore Parent Folder</b>\nThis option resets the selected folder's siblings and parent folder to their initial state."
    },
    "developer_comments": {
        "en-US": "Please suggest correct translations for the following strings in your native language. Your language will be added in the next version:\n\n<ol><li>Breakout Subfolders</li><li>Promote Subfolders</li><li>Restore Parent Folder</li><li>Flattened</li><li>Flattened Folders</li></ol>\nTranslations can be submitted to the <a href=\"https://github.com/NHellFire/flat-folder-tree-tb/issues\" rel=\"nofollow\">issue tracker</a>."
    },
